<node id="&quot;MONOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Jacques Monod is a scientist who conducted research on bacterial growth and eventually won a Nobel Prize."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a person who returned to Paris after a stay in California to continue his research at the Sorbonne and search for a problem to work on for his doctorate."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a researcher who had previously conducted experiments on single-celled protozoans and later switched to studying bacteria."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a researcher whose work on the regulation of β-galactosidase enzyme in E. coli was groundbreaking."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a scientist making progress in his research on bacteria and nutrition, and later enlists in the Army during World War II to avoid being drafted into menial administrative work."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is a scientist who proposed a unifying idea about the regulation of protein shape and activity by small molecules, connecting enzyme repression and feedback inhibition."&lt;SEP&gt;"Monod is mentioned in the context of serendipitous events in a scientist's journey, specifically with his odd growth curve."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1f209b073ddfae25ccbc5d6c4b1b3bdd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-888714c5372ef9cb4e814d728bea2660&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d38d288705562386af251bee72875b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e49097cc559bd14c5110941a42aea17a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49bfa1052e84e7aa01a370e4f56efa65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d18f6e866a72517f6e972803e28dfe90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94a8b002c80b038b73a7847ffd14aefa</data>
