  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Elephants are a type of large mammal often observed in the Serengeti."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elephants are complex organisms used as a comparison to _E. coli_ in discussions of biological regulation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elephants are mentioned alongside E. coli in the statement by Monod and Jacob, representing complex organisms."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elephants are mentioned in the context of regulating animal numbers in nature."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elephants are part of the ecosystem studied, demonstrating the application of general rules to understand population dynamics."</data>
