<node id="&quot;ALLOSTERIC INHIBITION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Allosteric Inhibition is a mechanism of regulation where the binding of a molecule at a site other than the active site alters the function of an enzyme."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a157a60869b9e5a3e3f626f68d50e561</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INDUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Induction is a mechanism of regulation where a substance binds to a repressor protein, causing it to detach and allowing gene expression."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a157a60869b9e5a3e3f626f68d50e561</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REPRESSION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Repression is a mechanism of regulation where a repressor protein binds to DNA, preventing gene expression."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a157a60869b9e5a3e3f626f68d50e561</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEGATIVE REGULATION&quot;">
