</node>
<node id="&quot;WORKERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Workers are female bees that perform various tasks within the hive, such as nursing, cleaning, and foraging."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 23}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRONES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drones are male bees whose primary role is to mate with the queen, though they do not contribute to the colony's work."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 23}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A hive is the home of a colony of honey bees, providing a structured environment for the bees to live and work."&lt;SEP&gt;"A structure where bees live and produce honey, often managed by the beekeeper."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the home and workplace of the bees where they store food and raise their young."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is the structure where honey bees live and store their food and raise their brood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5c906ee94509b925b684931925ed59d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9d3b8970106c262af65b92fb2a8f3b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31f0534d86c88f1bbe401b2604dbdc88</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey bees are a species of bees that live in colonies and produce honey, with distinct roles for workers, drones, and queens."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CROSSBREEDING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Crossbreeding is the process by which bees from different subspecies mate, potentially affecting the genetic purity of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NURSING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nursing is the care and feeding of young bees by worker bees, ensuring their survival and development."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLEANING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cleaning involves the removal of debris and waste from the hive, maintaining hygiene and cleanliness."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORAGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Foraging is the process by which worker bees collect nectar and pollen from flowers, bringing it back to the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEEDING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feeding involves the provision of food to the queen and young bees, ensuring their nutrition and health."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CARING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Caring for the queen and young bees involves various tasks such as feeding, grooming, and protecting them."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENETIC CONTINUITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Genetic continuity refers to the preservation of the genetic traits of a colony over generations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENETIC DIVERSITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Genetic diversity refers to the variety of genetic traits within a colony, which can be influenced by mating behaviors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENETIC PURITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Genetic purity refers to the uniformity of genetic traits within a colony, which can be affected by crossbreeding."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUPERSEDURE PROCESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Supersedure is the process by which a new queen replaces the old one within the hive, often due to the old queen's decline or failure."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWARMING PROCESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Swarming is the process by which a colony splits to form a new colony, often involving the loss of genetic purity if the new queen mates with foreign drones."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A new queen is a young queen bee that replaces the old queen during the supersedure process."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OLD QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An old queen is a queen bee that is replaced during the supersedure process, often due to age or decline."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;YOUNG BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Young bees are the developing bees within the hive, including larvae and pupae, which will eventually become workers or drones."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARVAE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Larvae are the immature stage of bees, which are fed and cared for by worker bees until they develop into adults."&lt;SEP&gt;"Larvae are the immature stages of honey bees, which require specific foods during their development."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5c906ee94509b925b684931925ed59d</data>
