<node id="&quot;CHEST REGISTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Chest Register is a vocal register that produces a rich, full sound and is used in music theater singing beyond the traditional classical shift."&lt;SEP&gt;"Chest register is a term used in vocal description, specifically mode 1, characterized by thyroarytenoid (TA) dominance and modal voice. It is crucial for singers, especially in musical theater, and is often used in conjunction with head register."&lt;SEP&gt;"chest register is a vocal technique characterized by thyroarytenoid (TA) dominance, chest mode, or modal voice.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f586118e4cd3d9e495c2d1ecb1dcfe1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THYROARYTENOID (TA)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Thyroarytenoid (TA) is a muscle in the larynx that plays a significant role in chest register, contributing to its characteristic sound."&lt;SEP&gt;"thyroarytenoid (TA) is a muscle in the larynx that plays a crucial role in voice production.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f586118e4cd3d9e495c2d1ecb1dcfe1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHEST MODE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"chest mode refers to a vocal technique where the sound is produced primarily in the chest cavity.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f586118e4cd3d9e495c2d1ecb1dcfe1b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MODAL VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Modal Voice is a vocal mode used in chest register."&lt;SEP&gt;"modal voice is a natural speaking voice that combines elements of both chest and head registers.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f586118e4cd3d9e495c2d1ecb1dcfe1b</data>
