  <data key="d1">"Tax matters refer to issues related to tax compliance and reporting.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f586118e4cd3d9e495c2d1ecb1dcfe1b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOPRANO OR LEGIT SINGING VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Soprano or legit singing voice is a type of voice similar to classical singing but with a brighter color, essential for female musical theater singers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Soprano or legit singing voice is a type of voice similar to classical singing except the color is brighter, essential for female musical theater singers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BELT VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Belt Voice is a vocal technique used in music theater that extends the speaking voice and is characterized by a mix of chest and head registers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Belt voice is a challenging vocal technique in musical theater, defined differently by various voice teachers, some considering it a chest register function above E4, while others view it as an extension of the speaking voice, rather than chest register taken higher than the standard pitch range of approximately E4. What is important to point out is that both chest register dominant singing and speaking use the throat muscle in a very similar way!"&lt;SEP&gt;"Belt voice is a challenging vocal technique in musical theater, defined differently by various voice teachers, some considering it a chest register function above E4, while others view it as an extension of the speaking voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REGISTRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Registration refers to the different modes of vocal fold vibration, including chest register and head register, which are important for singers to understand and utilize."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSICAL THEATER SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Musical theater singing involves the use of various vocal techniques, including chest register, head register, and belt voice, to perform songs and convey emotions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOICE TEACHERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Voice teachers are professionals who instruct singers on proper vocal techniques, including the use of chest register and other vocal modes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHEST REGISTER DOMINANT SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Chest register dominant singing is a vocal technique that emphasizes the use of the chest register, which is similar to speaking voice and uses the throat muscle in a similar manner."&lt;SEP&gt;"chest register dominant singing refers to a vocal technique where the singer uses the chest voice predominantly, similar to speaking but with a stronger resonance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3f3c8f816c3f21505f72df4a8ef298e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPEAKING VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Speaking voice is the natural voice used in everyday conversation, which shares similarities with chest register dominant singing in terms of throat muscle usage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MODE 1&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mode 1 is a term used to describe the chest register, characterized by thyroarytenoid (TA) dominance and modal voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MODE 2&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mode 2 is a term used to describe the head register, contrasting with mode 1 (chest register) in vocal fold vibration."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SINGING VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Singing Voice is the voice used for singing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Singing voice refers to the vocal technique used in singing, which can be categorized into different modes such as chest register, head register, and belt voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOPRANO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Soprano is a high-pitched singing voice, often used in classical and musical theater singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LEGIT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Legit is a term used to describe a singing voice that is similar to classical singing but with a brighter color, often used in musical theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BELT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ROLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Belt is a vocal technique used in musical theater, often associated with a powerful and resonant sound, sometimes considered a chest register function."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL FOLD VIBRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal fold vibration describes the physical process of sound production in the larynx, which can be categorized into different modes such as chest register and head register."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLASSICAL SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Classical singing is a style of singing that emphasizes clear diction, breath control, and a bright timbre, often used as a reference point for comparing other singing styles."&lt;SEP&gt;"Classical singing is a style of singing that emphasizes the use or addition of 'head' voice at the passaggio."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e4e181dd5099e0ad2640bc3700a9eb29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSICAL THEATER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Musical theater is a form of theater that combines music, song, spoken dialogue, and dance, often requiring singers to use various vocal techniques such as chest register, head register, and belt voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-aaef82ecc0d145507f39d0c24de7f95a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPEAKING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"speaking is the act of using the throat muscle, specifically the thyroarytenoid, in a similar way to chest register dominant singing, emphasizing the vocal muscle usage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3f3c8f816c3f21505f72df4a8ef298e3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BELT SOUND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"belt sound is a vocal technique characterized by loud, brassy, nasal, bright, forward, and 'ringy' qualities, commonly used in pop/rock musicals, especially in the C4–C5 octave, but now extended to higher octaves."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3f3c8f816c3f21505f72df4a8ef298e3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POP/ROCK MUSICAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"pop/rock musicals are theatrical productions that require a specific vocal technique known as the belt sound, often extending beyond the C5 octave."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3f3c8f816c3f21505f72df4a8ef298e3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLASSICAL VOCAL PRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"classical vocal production is a technique distinct from the belt voice, typically used in classical singing and considered different from the vocal demands of music theater singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3f3c8f816c3f21505f72df4a8ef298e3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPEECH EXERCISES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Speech Exercises are vocal exercises designed to help develop the mix/belt sound in music theater singing."&lt;SEP&gt;"speech exercises are advocated by many teachers to help create the mix/belt sound, blending elements of speaking and singing techniques."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f3c8f816c3f21505f72df4a8ef298e3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THYROARYTENOID&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"thyroarytenoid is a vocal muscle used in both speaking and chest register dominant singing, highlighting the similarity in vocal technique between these two activities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3f3c8f816c3f21505f72df4a8ef298e3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSIC THEATER SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Music Theater Singing refers to a style of singing that combines elements of both classical and popular singing techniques, often used in musical theater performances."&lt;SEP&gt;"music theater singing requires a vocal technique different from classical singing, emphasizing the distinction between the two styles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f3c8f816c3f21505f72df4a8ef298e3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEMALE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"female refers to a gender category, which is relevant in discussing vocal techniques and singing styles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3f3c8f816c3f21505f72df4a8ef298e3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIGH BELT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"high belt is a term used to describe the extension of the belt voice to higher octaves, often required in modern pop/rock musicals."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3f3c8f816c3f21505f72df4a8ef298e3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLASSICAL SINGING TECHNIQUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Classical Singing Technique refers to a traditional method of singing that emphasizes specific techniques and ranges, often used in opera and classical music performances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEMALE MUSIC THEATER SINGER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Female Music Theater Singer is a performer who specializes in music theater and uses techniques such as chest register and mix/belt sound."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLASSICAL SHIFT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Classical Shift is a point in classical singing where the voice typically shifts from chest to head register, usually around E or E flat above middle C."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MIX REGISTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mix Register is a blend of head and chest registers used in music theater singing, with a predominance of chest register."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOIX MIXTE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Voix Mixte is a term used in classical singing to describe the region of the voice where sensations of 'chest' and 'head' are experienced simultaneously."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ZONA DI PASSAGGIO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Zona di Passaggio is the region of the classical singing voice where sensations of 'chest' and 'head' are experienced simultaneously, as defined by vocal pedagogue Richard Miller."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSIC THEATER MIX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Music Theater Mix is a blend of head and chest registers with a predominance of chest register, used in music theater singing and having a lighter and more spoken quality compared to belt singing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Music theater mix is a vocal production style that combines elements of chest and head registers, used more extensively in music theater than in classical singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4e181dd5099e0ad2640bc3700a9eb29</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BELT SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Belt Singing is the sung extension of the 'calling voice' in music theater, characterized by a mix of chest and head registers with a predominance of chest register."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CALLING VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Calling Voice is the natural speaking voice of a singer, which can be extended into belt singing in music theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MIDDLE C&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Middle C is a specific note in music, often used as a reference point for pitch."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TA DOMINANT MODE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"TA Dominant Mode is a vocal mode used in chest register."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEAD REGISTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Head Register is a vocal register used in Voix Mixte."&lt;SEP&gt;"Head register refers to the upper part of the vocal range, characterized by a lighter and more spoken quality compared to the 'calling voice' used in belt singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c53f290cfdb325aa86cba150df1616e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4e181dd5099e0ad2640bc3700a9eb29</data>
</node>
