<node id="&quot;HONEY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"FOOD"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey is a sweet substance produced by bees from nectar, stored in the hive for food and energy reserves."&lt;SEP&gt;"Honey is a sweet substance produced by bees from nectar, used as a primary food source for the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Honey is described as a principal component of the adult honey bee's diet, derived from nectar."&lt;SEP&gt;"Honey is the sweet substance produced by bees from nectar, stored in the honey supers of the beehive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5c906ee94509b925b684931925ed59d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e783f6ef7fb844692e067fa1f0ed943&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e82a5adb056c9a3d09ee2e6abbd4d900&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0643cd32ffcc8ca5432a080d756a1be6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 48}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POLLEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pollen is a fine powder produced by plants that is collected by bees for food and to aid in plant reproduction."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pollen is a fine powder produced by plants, rich in proteins, fats, and carbohydrates, crucial for brood rearing and nutrition."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pollen is another principal component of the adult honey bee's diet, providing protein and fats."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pollen is the male reproductive part of a flower, collected by bees and used for protein and brood development."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5c906ee94509b925b684931925ed59d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e783f6ef7fb844692e067fa1f0ed943&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9d3b8970106c262af65b92fb2a8f3b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0643cd32ffcc8ca5432a080d756a1be6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 48}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ROYAL JELLY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"FOOD"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Royal Jelly is described as the first food for honey bee brood, a secretion from worker bees' heads."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0643cd32ffcc8ca5432a080d756a1be6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 49}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WORKER BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANISM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Worker Bees are female bees that perform various tasks within the hive, including collecting nectar and producing royal jelly."&lt;SEP&gt;"Worker bees are female bees that perform various tasks within the hive, including feeding the larvae with bee milk or royal jelly."&lt;SEP&gt;"Worker bees are mentioned as producing royal jelly and having glands for this purpose."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d5c906ee94509b925b684931925ed59d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0643cd32ffcc8ca5432a080d756a1be6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 49}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NECTAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nectar is a substance collected by bees for food and energy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is a sweet liquid produced by plants to attract pollinators, which bees collect to make honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is a watery secretion from flowers, primarily composed of sucrose, which bees collect to make honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is the source material for honey production, collected by bees from flowers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar is the sugary liquid produced by flowers that bees collect to make honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e82a5adb056c9a3d09ee2e6abbd4d900&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0643cd32ffcc8ca5432a080d756a1be6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9d3b8970106c262af65b92fb2a8f3b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e783f6ef7fb844692e067fa1f0ed943&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5c906ee94509b925b684931925ed59d</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 8}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 46}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 102}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARVAL STAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"STAGE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The larval stage is described as a part of the life cycle of honey bee brood, requiring specific food such as bee milk or royal jelly."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0643cd32ffcc8ca5432a080d756a1be6</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLD RAINY STRETCHES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cold rainy stretches are conditions that bees must prepare for, as they cannot leave the hive during these times."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0643cd32ffcc8ca5432a080d756a1be6</data>
