</node>
<node id="&quot;TIGERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANIMAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tigers are apex predators in a food chain, typically found at the top and are less abundant compared to animals at the base of the food chain."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5bc15638d83af338881cdee315b5d107</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PREY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANIMAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Prey refers to the animals at the base of the food chain that are consumed by predators like tigers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5bc15638d83af338881cdee315b5d107</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 122}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOOD CHAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Food chain describes the flow of energy and nutrients from one organism to another, starting from the base with primary producers and ending with apex predators like tigers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5bc15638d83af338881cdee315b5d107</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NUMBERS OF THE DIFFERENT KINDS OF ANIMALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Numbers of the different kinds of animals refer to the population sizes of various species within a food chain, typically more abundant at the base and fewer at the top."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5bc15638d83af338881cdee315b5d107</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PYRAMID OF NUMBERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pyramid of Numbers is a graphical representation of the numbers of organisms at different trophic levels in a food chain, showing abundance from the base to the apex."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Pyramid of Numbers is a concept describing the distribution of animal populations in a food chain, with more organisms at the base and fewer at the top."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e37e299e058af586e801321f6b6d35dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5bc15638d83af338881cdee315b5d107</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ONE HILL CANNOT SHELTER TWO TIGERS.&quot; &quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"This phrase indicates the limited space and resources available for apex predators like tigers, limiting their population size."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5bc15638d83af338881cdee315b5d107</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;APEX PREDATORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Apex predators are at the top of the food chain, having few natural predators and playing a crucial role in maintaining ecological balance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5bc15638d83af338881cdee315b5d107</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ECOLOGICAL BALANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Ecological balance refers to the stable state of a food chain where predator-prey relationships maintain a balanced population of organisms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5bc15638d83af338881cdee315b5d107</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 120}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEASIBILITY OF GETTING ENOUGH OF THE SMALLER FOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feasibility of getting enough of the smaller food refers to the availability of prey for animals at the base of the food chain."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5bc15638d83af338881cdee315b5d107</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 78}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 123}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PRIMARY PRODUCERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Primary producers are organisms at the base of the food chain, such as plants, which convert sunlight into energy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5bc15638d83af338881cdee315b5d107</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 17}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 77}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 122}]</data>
</node>
