</node>
<node id="&quot;STANDARD VEIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Standard Veil is a type of protective gear available in two styles, round or square, used for protection against stings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12b39c6792276dd0ee66f4e9e6ceb7b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ALEXANDER VEIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Alexander Veil is another type of protective veil used without a helmet, similar to a standard round veil but less satisfactory for long-term regular use."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12b39c6792276dd0ee66f4e9e6ceb7b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ROUND VEIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Round Veil is a specific style of standard veil that must be rolled and reshaped for each use."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12b39c6792276dd0ee66f4e9e6ceb7b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SQUARE VEIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Square Veil is a specific style of standard veil that can be removed from the helmet and folded when not in use."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12b39c6792276dd0ee66f4e9e6ceb7b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HELMET&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Helmet is mentioned as a component of standard veils, required for round veils but not for Alexander veils."&lt;SEP&gt;"helmet is a protective headgear used in beekeeping, often preferred over veils due to its stiffer brim, providing better protection but may be heavier and more cumbersome in warm weather."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12b39c6792276dd0ee66f4e9e6ceb7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31f0534d86c88f1bbe401b2604dbdc88</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NATURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ENVIRONMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nature is the context in which animal numbers are regulated."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12b39c6792276dd0ee66f4e9e6ceb7b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 72}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 119}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;APPLIED FIELDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"FIELD"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Applied Fields refer to practical applications of regulating animal numbers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12b39c6792276dd0ee66f4e9e6ceb7b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 72}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 119}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VEIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Veil is a protective head covering used in beekeeping to shield the face from bee stings."&lt;SEP&gt;"veil is a protective covering used in beekeeping, specifically designed to cover the head without a helmet, but requires reshaping for each use and can touch the beekeeper's face or head."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0fb5cd2d34f1365a33114f9f20fe12ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31f0534d86c88f1bbe401b2604dbdc88</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROAD-BRIMMED HAT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"broad-brimmed hat is a type of headwear that can serve as an alternative to a helmet or veil in beekeeping, offering protection and comfort."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-31f0534d86c88f1bbe401b2604dbdc88</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOVES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gloves are protective wear for the hands, useful for handling equipment and bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"gloves are protective wear used in beekeeping to protect the hands, especially during situations where bees may become agitated, but are not recommended for regular or long-term use due to the risk of crushing bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-87b58e4adf38ad0f5bfe32e07e21079f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31f0534d86c88f1bbe401b2604dbdc88</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRAME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A tool used in beekeeping to organize and manage the comb structure within the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-31f0534d86c88f1bbe401b2604dbdc88</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE BODY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A larger component of the hive used to house frames and store honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive Body refers to a component of a beehive used for housing the brood and bees, typically available in standard and mid-size options."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e82a5adb056c9a3d09ee2e6abbd4d900&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-31f0534d86c88f1bbe401b2604dbdc88</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 7}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPER'S GLOVES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beekeeper's Gloves are specialized protective gear designed for beekeepers to handle bees safely."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0fb5cd2d34f1365a33114f9f20fe12ff</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 50}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COVERALLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Coveralls are a type of protective clothing used in beekeeping, often paired with a separate veil, providing full-body protection."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coveralls are full-body protective clothing worn by beekeepers to shield from stings and debris."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0fb5cd2d34f1365a33114f9f20fe12ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87b58e4adf38ad0f5bfe32e07e21079f</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 50}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEE SUITS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bee Suits are protective garments worn by beekeepers, typically including a veil attached with a zipper, offering comprehensive coverage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0fb5cd2d34f1365a33114f9f20fe12ff</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 50}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN EXCLUDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Queen Excluder is a type of equipment used in beekeeping to separate the brood chamber from the honey supers, and can sometimes be used as a honey excluder."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen Excluder is a device used in hive management to prevent the queen bee from entering certain areas of the hive, useful for managing honey production."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen excluder is a device placed between supers and the brood chamber to prevent the queen from laying eggs in the honey supers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0fb5cd2d34f1365a33114f9f20fe12ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87b58e4adf38ad0f5bfe32e07e21079f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 51}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE MANAGEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive Management involves the care and maintenance of beehives, including tasks such as inspecting, feeding, and controlling the movement of the queen bee."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0fb5cd2d34f1365a33114f9f20fe12ff</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 50}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Supers are additional boxes added to a beehive to provide space for the bees to store honey or raise brood."&lt;SEP&gt;"Supers are containers placed on top of the hive body to collect honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0fb5cd2d34f1365a33114f9f20fe12ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOUNDATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Foundation is a sheet of wax or plastic used in supers to guide the bees in building comb."&lt;SEP&gt;"Foundation is a tool used by beginner beekeepers during the first season to encourage bees to build comb."&lt;SEP&gt;"Foundation is the base material provided for bees to build comb, often hook-wired with specific dimensions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0fb5cd2d34f1365a33114f9f20fe12ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87b58e4adf38ad0f5bfe32e07e21079f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 51}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NECTAR FLOW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nectar Flow refers to the period when flowers are blooming and bees are collecting nectar."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar Flow refers to the period when flowers are producing nectar, which bees collect to make honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0fb5cd2d34f1365a33114f9f20fe12ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 51}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beekeepers are individuals who manage and care for beehives, ensuring their health and productivity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeepers refer to the device as a 'honey excluder' and use it in specific situations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeepers refer to this device as a 'honey excluder,' and it can, in fact, act as such. One such situation involves a weak nectar flow and supers with foundation. The bees are decidedly reluctant to draw foundation above an excluder and a weak nectar flow compounds the problem. Beginners often deal with both conditions—they commonly use foundation during the first season, and place honey supers on the hive later in the season when nectar flows are slowing down."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY EXCLUDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Honey Excluder is a device used by beekeepers to prevent bees from accessing certain parts of the hive, often used in weak nectar flow situations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 51}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEGINNER BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beginner Beekeepers often use foundation and honey supers at inappropriate times and struggle with weak nectar flows."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 51}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY SUPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey Supers are additional boxes added above the brood chamber for honey storage, available in shallow or mid-depth sizes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Honey Supers are components of a beehive used for storing honey, often of a different size than the hive bodies."&lt;SEP&gt;"Honey Supers are containers placed on top of the hive body to collect honey, often used later in the season when nectar flows are slowing down."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-87b58e4adf38ad0f5bfe32e07e21079f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e82a5adb056c9a3d09ee2e6abbd4d900</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EQUIPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Equipment includes various tools and devices used in beekeeping, such as honey excluders, queen excluders, and honey supers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 51}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CATALOGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Catalogs offer a wide range of beekeeping equipment, which can be overwhelming for beginners."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 51}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TWO FULL-DEPTH, TEN-FRAME HIVE BODIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Two Full-Depth, Ten-Frame Hive Bodies is a common configuration for beehives."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACTIVE BEEKEEPING SEASON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Active Beekeeping Season is the period when beekeepers are actively managing their hives."&lt;SEP&gt;"Active beekeeping season is the period when beekeeping activities are most intense and productive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TWO-STORY HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Two-Story Hive is a specific configuration of beehive equipment, consisting of two full-depth, ten-frame hive bodies and honey supers, commonly used in beekeeping."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BOTTOM BOARD WITH ENTRANCE REDUCER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EQUIPMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bottom Board with Entrance Reducer is a component of the beehive that provides a base and controls the entry point for bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca</data>
