<edge source="&quot;ENZYME&quot;" target="&quot;INHIBITOR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The inhibitor binds to the active site of the enzyme, preventing the enzyme from catalyzing its normal reaction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-84496fb708a25e971b88a44322481b48</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME&quot;" target="&quot;SUBSTRATE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The substrate binds to the active site of the enzyme, which is altered by the inhibitor, preventing the substrate from fitting."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-84496fb708a25e971b88a44322481b48</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME&quot;" target="&quot;ACTIVE SITE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The enzyme has an active site where the substrate binds and undergoes catalysis."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-84496fb708a25e971b88a44322481b48</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME&quot;" target="&quot;BUCKFAST HYBRID&quot;">
  <data key="d4">15.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Enzymes are a type of molecule that plays a crucial role in maintaining specific ranges within the body, similar to how the Buckfast hybrid maintains specific characteristics."&lt;SEP&gt;"Enzymes are a type of molecule that plays a crucial role in maintaining specific ranges within the body, which is similar to how the Buckfast hybrid maintains specific characteristics."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f9d1f7e97654abe5710b4d3fcd811747</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ENZYME&quot;" target="&quot;ENZYME&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Enzymes are a type of molecule that plays a crucial role in maintaining specific ranges within the body, which is a fundamental aspect of life at the molecular level."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f9d1f7e97654abe5710b4d3fcd811747</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INHIBITOR&quot;" target="&quot;ACTIVE SITE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The inhibitor binds to the active site of the enzyme, preventing the enzyme from catalyzing its normal reaction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-84496fb708a25e971b88a44322481b48</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SUBSTRATE&quot;" target="&quot;ACTIVE SITE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The substrate binds to the active site of the enzyme, which is altered by the inhibitor, preventing the substrate from fitting."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-84496fb708a25e971b88a44322481b48</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;" target="&quot;LACTOSE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"When lactose binds to the repressor, it changes the shape of the repressor, preventing it from binding to DNA and allowing the enzyme gene to turn on."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-84496fb708a25e971b88a44322481b48</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;" target="&quot;SHAPE CHANGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The shape of the repressor changes when it binds to lactose, which affects its ability to bind to DNA."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-84496fb708a25e971b88a44322481b48</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;" target="&quot;GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The repressor binds to DNA and can inhibit the expression of the gene."&lt;SEP&gt;"The repressor prevents the gene from turning on by binding to DNA."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-84496fb708a25e971b88a44322481b48&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49bfa1052e84e7aa01a370e4f56efa65</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;" target="&quot;MONOD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Monod proposed a unifying idea involving the repressor, connecting enzyme repression and feedback inhibition."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-49bfa1052e84e7aa01a370e4f56efa65</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;" target="&quot;INDUCER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Inducer affects the Repressor by changing its shape."&lt;SEP&gt;"The inducer binds to the repressor, causing a change in its shape and allowing the gene to turn on."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-49bfa1052e84e7aa01a370e4f56efa65</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;" target="&quot;ALLOSTERY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Allostery explains how the binding of the inducer to the repressor changes its shape."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-49bfa1052e84e7aa01a370e4f56efa65</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;" target="&quot;ENZYME GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The repressor can affect the Enzyme Gene by binding to DNA."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-49bfa1052e84e7aa01a370e4f56efa65</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;" target="&quot;CELL MULTIPLICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Repressors play a crucial role in controlling cell multiplication, and their inactivation can lead to changes in this process."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b932cf141ea62f3f4599201ad78d0ee1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LACTOSE&quot;" target="&quot;SHAPE CHANGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Lactose binding to the repressor causes a shape change, which allows the enzyme gene to turn on."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-84496fb708a25e971b88a44322481b48</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MONOD&quot;" target="&quot;INDUCER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Monod's idea involves the inducer, a small molecule that can bind to the repressor and change its shape."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-49bfa1052e84e7aa01a370e4f56efa65</data>
