  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COMPANY SPECIFIED REPRESENTATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;SECTION 5.1&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Company Specified Representations contain the representations and warranties in the first sentence of Section 5.1."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a1ad75b34be8f4c2caafc2636cd25519</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COMPANY SPECIFIED REPRESENTATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;SECTION 5.3&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Company Specified Representations contain the representations and warranties in Section 5.3."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a1ad75b34be8f4c2caafc2636cd25519</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COMPANY SPECIFIED REPRESENTATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;SECTION 5.9&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Company Specified Representations contain the representations and warranties in Section 5.9."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a1ad75b34be8f4c2caafc2636cd25519</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CONFIRMATION ORDER&quot;" target="&quot;RESTRUCTURING TERM SHEET&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Confirmation Order is defined in the Restructuring Term Sheet."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a1ad75b34be8f4c2caafc2636cd25519</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESTRUCTURING TERM SHEET&quot;" target="&quot;FORMER OR CURRENT PRODUCTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Any defects or quality issues related to Former or Current Products are part of the Restructuring Term Sheet and related documents, and no Causes of Action are pending or threatened against the Company or its Subsidiaries."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-aa7e3853e32e9f1fed01da5b53618aca</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESTRUCTURING TERM SHEET&quot;" target="&quot;COMPANY DISCLOSURE LETTER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">28.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Company Disclosure Letter is part of the Restructuring Term Sheet and related documents, and no Causes of Action are pending or threatened against the Company or its Subsidiaries."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-aa7e3853e32e9f1fed01da5b53618aca</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESTRUCTURING TERM SHEET&quot;" target="&quot;EMPLOYEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Employees must follow the terms and conditions outlined in the Restructuring Term Sheet during the Effective Period."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2593429f6940c350a32ac9825a7bf86a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESTRUCTURING TERM SHEET&quot;" target="&quot;GOVERNMENTAL ENTITIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Governmental Entities must ensure compliance with the terms and conditions outlined in the Restructuring Term Sheet during the Effective Period."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2593429f6940c350a32ac9825a7bf86a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESTRUCTURING TERM SHEET&quot;" target="&quot;EFFECTIVE PERIOD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Effective Period must adhere to the terms and conditions outlined in the Restructuring Term Sheet."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2593429f6940c350a32ac9825a7bf86a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESTRUCTURING TERM SHEET&quot;" target="&quot;DIP AGENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Restructuring Term Sheet must adhere to the actions approved by the DIP Agent."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2593429f6940c350a32ac9825a7bf86a</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FLEET HERDS OF GRAZING ANIMALS&quot;" target="&quot;WILY PREDATORS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"fleet herds of grazing animals and wily predators maintain a natural balance in the ecosystem through predator-prey interactions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;OLDUVAI&quot;" target="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Olduvai provides evidence of early human activity, including the use of stone tools and butchery marks, indicating the presence of Homo sapiens."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;OLDUVAI&quot;" target="&quot;STONE TOOLS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Olduvai provides evidence of the use of stone tools by early humans, indicating their ability to adapt and innovate."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;SMALLPOX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Homo sapiens were affected by smallpox, a highly contagious and deadly virus, which had a significant impact on human populations in the early 20th century."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;TUBERCULOSIS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Homo sapiens were affected by tuberculosis, a widespread and deadly bacterial disease, particularly in urban areas during the 19th century."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;CONTROL OF BIOLOGY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"In the past century, Homo sapiens have gained control over biological processes, such as eradicating smallpox and managing tuberculosis."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;ADAPTATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Homo sapiens have adapted to environmental changes and technological advancements, allowing them to take control of biological processes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;FAMINE AND EPIDEMICS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Homo sapiens were vulnerable to the effects of famine and epidemics, highlighting the challenges faced by early human societies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;FARMING AND CIVILIZATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The advent of farming and civilization allowed Homo sapiens to settle in permanent locations, reducing vulnerability to the whims of the weather."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;WEATHER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Homo sapiens were vulnerable to the effects of weather, which influenced their survival and migration patterns."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;CITIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The development of cities provided protection and resources, but also increased vulnerability to diseases like tuberculosis."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;SMALLPOX AND TUBERCULOSIS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Homo sapiens were affected by both smallpox and tuberculosis, highlighting the ongoing struggle against infectious diseases."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;BIOLOGICAL CONTROL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Biology controlled Homo sapiens for most of their existence, but in recent times, they have taken control of biological processes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;MEDICAL ADVANCEMENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Medical advancements have played a crucial role in controlling biological threats like smallpox and tuberculosis."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL ADAPTATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Homo sapiens have adapted to various environments, from nomadic lifestyles to settled civilizations, showcasing their resilience."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;TECHNOLOGICAL ADVANCEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Technological advancements have enabled Homo sapiens to take control of biological processes, marking a significant shift in their relationship with nature."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;ECOSYSTEM BALANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Homo sapiens have impacted the ecosystem balance through their actions, both positively and negatively."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;PREDATOR-PREY DYNAMICS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Homo sapiens have influenced predator-prey dynamics through their hunting practices and the domestication of animals."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;STONE TOOL USE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The use of stone tools by Homo sapiens indicates their ability to adapt and innovate, contributing to their survival and success."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;URBANIZATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Urbanization has provided new challenges and opportunities for Homo sapiens, particularly in terms of health and disease management."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;FAMINE PREVENTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Homo sapiens have developed strategies to prevent famine, such as agriculture and food storage, improving their chances of survival."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-2ed3446b08c742065c1f458e60582445</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HOMO SAPIENS&quot;" target="&quot;EPIDEMIC CONTROL&quot;">
