<edge source="&quot;ITALIAN DRONES&quot;" target="&quot;HYBRID QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">21.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hybrid queens may mate with Italian drones, potentially affecting the genetic lineage of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Italian drones are likely to mate with a hybrid queen, potentially affecting the genetic lineage of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Italian drones are likely to mate with a random queen, including a hybrid queen, potentially affecting the genetic lineage."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYBRID QUEEN&quot;" target="&quot;REQUEENING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hybrid queens may require requeening more frequently to prevent genetic dilution through crossbreeding during supersedure or swarming."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REQUEENING&quot;" target="&quot;SUPERSEDURE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Requeening is necessary to avoid genetic dilution during supersedure, where a new queen replaces the old one."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REQUEENING&quot;" target="&quot;SWARMING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Requeening is also important to prevent genetic dilution during swarming, where the colony splits and forms a new one."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SUPERSEDURE&quot;" target="&quot;SWARMING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Supersedure and swarming both involve the replacement of the queen, which can affect the genetic purity of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;WORKERS&quot;" target="&quot;DRONES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Drones do not directly interact with workers, but their presence affects the overall genetic health of the colony through mating with the queen."&lt;SEP&gt;"Workers indirectly influence drones by supporting the queen, who in turn produces drones."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-d9b4287519d636f7aae117d4276d53d6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
