<edge source="&quot;HELMET&quot;" target="&quot;VEIL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">84.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Helmet and veil are both protective headgear used in beekeeping, with helmets generally being heavier and more cumbersome in warm weather, while veils require reshaping for each use and can touch the beekeeper's face or head."&lt;SEP&gt;"The veil and helmet are both used by the beekeeper to protect their head during beekeeping tasks."&lt;SEP&gt;"The veil is an alternative to the helmet, providing similar protection but requiring more frequent reshaping."&lt;SEP&gt;"Veil is an alternative to helmet in beekeeping, but unlike helmets, veils require reshaping for each use and can touch the beekeeper's face or head, making them less satisfactory for long-term regular use."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-31f0534d86c88f1bbe401b2604dbdc88</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HELMET&quot;" target="&quot;BROAD-BRIMMED HAT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">110.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Broad-brimmed hat and helmet are both protective headgear used in beekeeping, with broad-brimmed hats offering a lighter and more comfortable option compared to helmets that are generally heavier and more cumbersome in warm weather."&lt;SEP&gt;"Broad-brimmed hat is an alternative to helmet in providing head protection, offering a lighter and more comfortable option compared to helmets that are generally heavier and more cumbersome in warm weather."&lt;SEP&gt;"Helmet and broad-brimmed hat are both protective headgear used in beekeeping, with broad-brimmed hats offering a lighter and more comfortable option compared to helmets that are generally heavier and more cumbersome in warm weather."&lt;SEP&gt;"Helmet and broad-brimmed hat both provide head protection in beekeeping, with helmets generally being heavier and more cumbersome in warm weather, while broad-brimmed hats offer a lighter and more comfortable option."&lt;SEP&gt;"The helmet and broad-brimmed hat are both used by the beekeeper to protect their head and manage the comb structure during beekeeping tasks."&lt;SEP&gt;"The helmet and broad-brimmed hat are both used by the beekeeper to protect their head during beekeeping tasks."&lt;SEP&gt;"The helmet is an alternative to the broad-brimmed hat, providing similar protection but being heavier and more cumbersome in warm weather."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-31f0534d86c88f1bbe401b2604dbdc88</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HELMET&quot;" target="&quot;GLOVES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">93.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Gloves and helmet are both protective gear used in beekeeping, but gloves are used to protect the hands while helmets are used to cover the head, with gloves not recommended for regular or long-term use due to the risk of crushing bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Gloves are an alternative to helmets in protecting the hands during beekeeping, but unlike helmets, gloves are not recommended for regular or long-term use due to the risk of crushing bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Helmet and gloves are both protective gear used in beekeeping, but helmets are used to cover the head while gloves are used to protect the hands, with gloves not recommended for regular or long-term use due to the risk of crushing bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"The helmet and gloves are both used by the beekeeper to protect their hands during beekeeping tasks."&lt;SEP&gt;"The helmet and gloves are both used by the beekeeper to protect their head and hands during beekeeping tasks."&lt;SEP&gt;"The helmet and gloves are both used by the beekeeper to protect themselves during beekeeping tasks."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-31f0534d86c88f1bbe401b2604dbdc88</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
