<edge source="&quot;BEGINNER BEEKEEPERS&quot;" target="&quot;EXPERIENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">96.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Experience helps Beginner Beekeepers make better judgments about when to use Honey Excluders, Queen Excluders, and Honey Supers."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEGINNER BEEKEEPERS&quot;" target="&quot;WEAK NECTAR FLOW&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beginner Beekeepers struggle with timing the placement of Honey Supers based on Weak Nectar Flow."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY SUPERS&quot;" target="&quot;WEAK NECTAR FLOW&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Honey Supers are placed on the hive later in the season when Nectar Flow is weak."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY SUPERS&quot;" target="&quot;EXPERIENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">84.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Experience helps in understanding the proper use of Honey Supers in Weak Nectar Flow situations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Experience helps in understanding the proper use of Honey Supers."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY SUPERS&quot;" target="&quot;MID-SIZE BOXES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Using mid-size boxes for both hive bodies and honey supers simplifies hive management by maintaining uniformity in box sizes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e82a5adb056c9a3d09ee2e6abbd4d900</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY SUPERS&quot;" target="&quot;STANDARD TWO DEEP HIVE BODIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both configurations contribute to the overall structure and functionality of the beehive, though they serve different purposes."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e82a5adb056c9a3d09ee2e6abbd4d900</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HONEY SUPERS&quot;" target="&quot;BEEHIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Honey Supers are components of a beehive used for storing honey."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e82a5adb056c9a3d09ee2e6abbd4d900</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EQUIPMENT&quot;" target="&quot;CATALOGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Catalogs offer a wide range of Equipment, which can be overwhelming for beginners."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EQUIPMENT&quot;" target="&quot;EXPERIENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">117.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Experience helps in making informed decisions about purchasing Equipment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Once you have some Experience, you will better understand the Catalog offerings and can begin to pick and choose."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-96b4a4cce7aa1e0c968a487c1d34a141</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ACTIVE BEEKEEPING SEASON&quot;" target="&quot;HIVES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hives are managed during the active beekeeping season."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TWO-STORY HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;BOTTOM BOARD WITH ENTRANCE REDUCER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Bottom Board with Entrance Reducer is a component of the Two-Story Hive, providing a base and controlling the entry point for bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TWO-STORY HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE BODIES (TWO)&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hive Bodies (two) are part of the Two-Story Hive, forming the main structure of the beehive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TWO-STORY HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;FRAMES (TEN PER HIVE BODY)&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Frames (ten per hive body) are part of the Two-Story Hive, holding the beeswax foundation and supporting the bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TWO-STORY HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;FOUNDATION—HOOK-WIRED, 8½-INCH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Foundation—hook-wired, 8½-inch is part of the Two-Story Hive, providing a surface for the bees to build comb on."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TWO-STORY HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;SUPPORT PINS (FOUR PER FRAME)&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Support Pins (four per frame) are part of the Two-Story Hive, securing the frames within the hive bodies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEGINNER&quot;" target="&quot;STANDARDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beginners should follow the standards."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EIGHT-FRAME AND ELEVEN-FRAME UNITS&quot;" target="&quot;STANDARDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"These are less common than the standard."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NARROWER AND WIDER BOXES&quot;" target="&quot;STANDARDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"These are alternatives to the standard."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-59c25b7703063039a7f9f7f2e34cf7ca</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;STANDARD TWO DEEP HIVE BODIES&quot;" target="&quot;MID-SIZE BOXES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both configurations provide similar interior volumes, allowing for flexibility in hive construction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e82a5adb056c9a3d09ee2e6abbd4d900</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;STANDARD TWO DEEP HIVE BODIES&quot;" target="&quot;WEIGHT REDUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Using mid-size boxes instead of standard two deep hive bodies reduces the overall weight of the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e82a5adb056c9a3d09ee2e6abbd4d900</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MID-SIZE BOXES&quot;" target="&quot;WEIGHT REDUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mid-Size Boxes reduce the weight of the hive, making it easier to handle."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e82a5adb056c9a3d09ee2e6abbd4d900</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
